@RonnyPfannschmidt just to be clear:

```python
@pytest.mark.parametrize("argument", ["baz"], indirect=True)
def test_without_argument(fixture):
    assert "baz" == fixture
```

(`indirect=["argument"]` would also be valid)

I agree, if `indirect` not given we should raise an explicit error requiring `indirect=True` or `indirect=["argument"]`.

Updated the labels to reflect that.
